  <span id="freeText10886215975321397257" style="display:none"><b>3.5 Stars</b><br />This is a wonderfully deep and complex fantasy series. As a science fiction reader, I particularly love the hints of sci-fi hidden within the story. The author does not info dump at all, but rather slowly reveals the world throughout the course of the story. Readers are told to very patient and pay attention to the small details, which should eventually provide deeper meaning. Admittedly, I wanted more from these first two volumes and became impatient for the world to reveal itself. <br /><br />On the surface level, the story is not difficult to follow yet so much more is hidden underneath. The prose itself was beautiful without ever being flowery or too dense. I appreciate the use of vocabulary, which brought more to the reading experience. <br /><br />This was my first time reading through the series and undoubtedly I know I did not pick up all the nuances on my first pass. I understand that readers often read this series multiple times and I can completely understand why. It's hard to review the series at this point because I need to see the payoff at the end in order to interpret what I've read so far.<br /><br />Overall, I really enjoyed this one and would highly recommend it to seasoned fantasy and science fiction readers alike. I am thankful that it is getting a new life within the Tor Essentials line.<br /><br />Disclaimer: I received the second bindup of this series from the publisher for review.</span>
