  <span id="freeText4393105064232307084" style="display:none">This was my first foray into the writing of Gene Wolfe and, I find myself asking, why did it take me so long? This was an absolutely incredible book.<br /><br />Wolfe's prose is extremely poetic and whimsical. Reading this novel is dream-like, almost trance-like; very few times have I read something that has so thoroughly taken me straight out of reality. Gorgeous writing.<br /><br />The story itself isn't quite as strong as Wolfe's writing ability however. The first half of the book, 'Shadow of the Torturer' is definitely the better installment than the second, 'Claw of the Conciliator'. That being said the second half certainly had some creative chapters that were mind blowing...namely one short story that is read by the main character 'Severian' to his injured associate. <br /><br />This novel is defined as a science-fiction novel. While that may technically be the case, it certainly does not read like one. <br /><br />I'm hesitant to recommend this novel to everyone; I would say it is an acquired literary taste. However, for those that have the imagination, attention span and open mind to enjoy reading this type of book, you will be immensely rewarded for your time and effort.</span>
